d restrictions, semantics and pragmatics, foreign word-formation, language planning and purism, historical word-formation, word-formation in language acquisition and aphasia, word-formation and language use, tools in word-formation research. The final chapter comprises 74 portraits of word-formation in the individual languages of Europe and offers an innovative perspective. These portraits afford the first overview of this kind and will prove useful for future typological research. This handbook will provide an essential reference for both advanced students and researchers in word-formation and related fields within linguistics.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aGerman languagevTextbooks for foreign speakers. 0aGerman languagexStudy and teachingxForeign speakers. 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxMorphology. 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxWord formation. 0aLinguistics. 4aMorphologie. 4aWord-Formation, Morphology, Language Typology, European Languages. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Morphology.2bisacsh1 aMüller, Peter O., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aOhnheiser, Ingeborg, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aOlsen, Susan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRainer, Franz, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE HSK 2015z9783110439670oZDB-23-DGS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE HSK 2016z9783110485196oZDB-23-DGS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE HSK 2018z9783110548280